    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-09-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-09-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="197"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d197">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <gloss target="#t_IO1">IO</gloss> Files</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum of Conversation, by Miss Elizabeth Gough of the
                        Office of United Nations Political and Security Affairs</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/> US/A/3314</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-09-27">September 27,
                            1951</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Subject: Chinese Representation</p>
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell rendition="#top #nowrap">Participants:</cell>
                        <cell>Miss Barbara Salt, British Embassy</cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Mr. Allen, <gloss target="#t_EUR1">EUR</gloss>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <cell/>
                        <cell>Miss Gough, <gloss target="#t_UNP1">UNP</gloss>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
                <p>[Here follows discussion of other matters.]</p>
                <p>3. <hi rend="italic">General Assembly</hi>
                </p>
                <p>Miss Salt informed us that the Foreign Office has sent a telegram to <gloss
                        target="#t_UKUN1">UKUN</gloss> requesting the Mission to work out with
                        <gloss target="#t_USUN1">USUN</gloss> the Chinese <pb facs="0286" n="264"
                        xml:id="pg_264"/> representation procedure for the Sixth <gloss
                        target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>. The highlights of this telegram were as follows:
                        (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) the UK agreed to follow the moratorium procedure
                    for the <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss>: (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) the
                    Foreign Office thought that the procedural motion might “best be made at the
                    opening session”: and (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) the UK preferred that the
                    motion be purely procedural with no reference in the text to the February 1
                    resolution or continuing aggression.</p>
            </div>
